What you need to know:

Generally, ticks are developing resistance to commonly used acaricides. There are several reasons attributed to this problem and most of them are management/application related.Greens/weeds harvested from the field might contain poisonous plants but usually, commercial feeds are safe only when all the requirements on storage and transportation/application are adhered to.There are so many crops that can do well in Nyanza. Watermelons, sweet potatoes, tomatoes, sorghum, millet, mangoes, pawpaw, oranges, bananas and indigenous vegetables like cowpea, spider plant, terere and black nightshade all perform well.